column11:
Affordability Indicator #1: 
Diet costs as % of global $1.90 poverty line available for food expenditures 
($1.20/day)
column14:
Affordability Indicator #2:  
Diet costs as % of country average food expenditures per capita from national accounts data
column17:
Affordability Indicator #3: 
Percent of population who cannot afford each diet, for whom diet costs >63% of hhld income
column20: Affordability Indicator #4: Number of people who cannot afford each diet, for whom diet costs >63% of hhld income (millions)
column23: Lower bound on indicator #3 (allows food budget up to 100% of income)
column26: Lower bound on indicator #4 (allows food budget up to 100% of income)
column29:
Upper bound on indicator #3 
(allows food budget up to mean for the country's WB income classification)
column32:
Upper bound on indicator #4 
(allows food budget up to mean for the country's WB income classification)
column35: Appendix data (CoNA, using RDA instead of EAR for nutrient requirements)
